##
## Cantilever beam bending test for UP (u-p) formulation — refined mesh
##   Mesh: 10x2x2 hex (40 elements), L=5, b=h=1
##   Material: E=1000, nu=0.499999 (nearly incompressible)
##   Load: tip concentrated force F=-2.0 (y-dir) at 3 nodes (LOAD_TIP)
##         F_per_node = -2/3 = -0.6667
##   BC: fixed end x=0 (FIX_X)
##   Solver: MUMPS direct, NLSTATIC 10 substeps
##
## Purpose:
##   Show convergence toward Timoshenko beam theory with mesh refinement
##   while maintaining volumetric-locking-free behavior (UP formulation).
##
## Results (step 10, full load):
##   UP:  tip deflection uy = -0.955 ( 92% of Timoshenko theory)
##   FI:  tip deflection uy = -0.031 (  3% of Timoshenko theory) <- locking!
##   Timoshenko theory:       -1.036
##   Volume change: UP -0.058%, FI -0.002%
##   Refinement 5x1x1 -> 10x2x2: UP improves 132% -> 92% (converging).
##   FI remains locked at ~3% regardless of mesh refinement.
##
!VERSION
 3
!SOLUTION, TYPE=NLSTATIC
!WRITE,LOG
!WRITE,RESULT
!SOLVER,METHOD=MUMPS,ITERLOG=NO,TIMELOG=NO
 10000, 1
 1.0e-08, 1.00, 0.0
!BOUNDARY, GRPID=1
 FIX_X,1,1
 FIX_X,2,2
 FIX_X,3,3
!CLOAD, GRPID=1
 LOAD_TIP,2,-0.666666666667
!MATERIAL, NAME=MAT1
!ELASTIC
 1.0000E+03, 4.99999E-01
!SECTION, SECNUM=1, FORM361=UP
!STEP, SUBSTEPS=10, CONVERG=1.0E-06
 BOUNDARY,1
 LOAD,1
!END
